ce:section.ce:para:
The developed sensing method using GQDs was successfully applied for analyzing lamivudine in pharmaceutical formulations and spiked plasma samples. In the analysis of pharmaceutical formulations, the concentration of lamivudine in different commercially available tablets was determined with a mean recovery value of 101.27 % ± 1.904. The results were compared for their mean and variance with a reported chromatographic method [8], and no significant difference was observed, indicating the accuracy and reliability of the developed CQD-based method (Table 2
                        ). In the analysis of spiked plasma samples, the developed method showed excellent performance. The recovery values ranged from 90-103 %, indicating the high accuracy and reliability of the method in quantifying lamivudine in biological samples (Table 3
                        ). Moreover, the CV values for the spiked plasma samples were below 10 %, indicating good precision of the method (Table 3).
